  "buggy_functions": ["video_detect_dmi_table"],
  "confidence": 0.95,
  "reasoning": "The Acer TravelMate 5735Z is missing from the video_detect_dmi_table in drivers/acpi/video_detect.c. This causes the system to default to ACPI video backlight (acpi_backlight_video) instead of native backlight (acpi_backlight_native). The bug report demonstrates that native backlight works properly on this hardware, while the default ACPI video backlight does not. The system needs a DMI quirk entry with the video_detect_force_native callback to select native backlight by default. The entry should match on DMI_SYS_VENDOR='Acer' and DMI_PRODUCT_NAME='TravelMate 5735Z', following the pattern of other non-Win8 systems in the table that require native backlight (lines 286-354)."
}

